article.headline: Bradley 82, ETSU 69
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- Dodie Dunson scored 17 points and Chris Roberts added 16 points, and each had four 3-pointers, to lead Bradley to a 82-69 win over East Tennessee State on Saturday. It was an even effort from Bradley (4-2), which also earned 12 points and a team-high eight rebounds from Theron Wilson and ten points from Eddren McCain. The Braves shot 57.8 percent from the field for the game. They led 44-25 at the break. Bradley had 22 points off its bench. Courtney Pigram led East Tennessee State (3-3) with 27 points and four rebounds. Kevin Tiggs had 15 points and five rebounds. East Tennessee State came back to score 44 points in the second half and improve its shooting percentage to 51.4 percent from 33.3 percent in the first half. East Tennessee scored 17 points off Bradley turnovers and had 17 points from fast breaks.
